        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 12:31PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1231 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
west of Short, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Alma...                           Figure Five...
Lee Creek...                      Natural Dam...
Uniontown...                      Furry...
Cedarville...                     Short...
Rudy...                           Van Buren...

This includes the following highways,
Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 11 and 13.
Interstate 49 between mile markers 22 and 25.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
